<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4615416-michael-jones"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1326815482i/4615416._UX100_CR0,19,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4615416-michael-jones">Michael Jones</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This version actually has a chapter which starts with: &quot;This chapter did not appear in the original British edition of this book...&quot; [because of a law<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This version actually has a chapter which starts with: "This chapter did not appear in the original British edition of this book..." [because of a lawsuit at the time] - so presumably it is an American edition. The Copyright notice lists all three years 2008, 2009, 2010.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
