      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/1387272.Ben_Goldacre">About Ben Goldacre</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/1387272.Ben_Goldacre"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1285983498p3/1387272.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/1387272.Ben_Goldacre">Ben Goldacre
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
899
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6094134427849323836">Ben Goldacre is a British science writer and psychiatrist, born in 1974. He is the author of The Guardian newspaper&apos;s weekly Bad Science column and a book of the same title, published by Fourth Estate in September 2008.<br/><br/>Goldacre is the son of Michael Goldacre, professor of public health at the University of Oxford, the nephew of science journalist Robyn Williams, and the great-great-grandson of Sir</span>
  <span id="freeText6094134427849323836" style="display:none">Ben Goldacre is a British science writer and psychiatrist, born in 1974. He is the author of The Guardian newspaper's weekly Bad Science column and a book of the same title, published by Fourth Estate in September 2008.<br /><br />Goldacre is the son of Michael Goldacre, professor of public health at the University of Oxford, the nephew of science journalist Robyn Williams, and the great-great-grandson of Sir Henry Parkes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6094134427849323836" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

